      <def-list content-type="enumerate" html:style="content: '(' counter(counter) ')'" html:type="1">
        <def-item html:value="1" id="ltxid5">
          <term>(1)</term> <def><p>In the LaTeX output, the background color extends to empty cells but not “undefined” cells (cf. the first two rows and the third column). In the texml output, we supply empty cells for all undefined cells in order to preserve cell borders, so blank cells become shaded. If we ever care, we can presumably deal with this by adding some CSS rules to zero out the color properties on filler cells. Or something.</p></def></def-item>
